description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;AIM OF THE ROLE:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist and support the professional staff within the Imaging Directorate maintaining a high standard of patient care by carrying out assigned tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide an efficient and reliable system for throughput of patients ensuring the activity and needs of the unit are achieved&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with clerical needs of the unit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Key working relationships&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Major working relationships with all Imaging staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaison with other clinical professionals, support staff, patients, carers and their relatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaison with other agencies, transport (porters/London Ambulance Service), NHS supplies etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Key result areas:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with patient care whilst supporting the professional team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively and ensure the smooth running of the service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a safe working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform clerical duties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stock and equipment maintenance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MAIN TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assist with patient care whilst supporting the Professional team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.1 Identify patients correctly using departmental Protocols and Procedures&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.2 Receive patients into the department and prepare them for their examination&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.3 To have a clear understanding of all procedures carried out within the Ultrasound Unit and the preparation required prior to the examination&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.4 Provide support and information to patients, carers and relatives where appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.5 Escort patients to the toilet as required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.6 Support the radiographic and radiological staff when undertaking procedures and chaperone&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;during intimate examinations as appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.7 Use equipment and accessories appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.8 Ensure all patient appointments are kept to time to aid in the smooth running of the unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.9 Care for bed bound patients awaiting their examination within the Imaging department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.10 Provide annual leave and sickness cover for colleagues as appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.11 &lt;em&gt;Un&lt;/em&gt;dertake any other duties requested as appropriate to the banding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1.12 To actively participate in out of hours duties where required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communicate effectively and ensure the smooth running of the service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2.1 To ensure effective communication with other staff and members of the public maintaining confidentiality at all times&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2.2 Ensure that enquiries are dealt with promptly and efficiently&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2.3 Attend staff meetings and contribute towards the smooth running of the clinical area&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2.4 Run errands within the hospital (including pharmacy) at the discretion of the radiographic and nursing staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2.5 To be prepared to work flexible hours according to the needs of the service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2.6 To participate in audit and quality control programmes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maintain a safe working environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3.1 To maintain a clean and safe working environment within the department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3.2 Ensure that all standard procedures, protocols and guidelines are adhered to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3.3 Have an understanding of the policies and procedures within the Imaging department and the Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3.4 Report any incidents/accidents and broken equipment to the appropriate person&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Perform clerical duties&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4.1 To assist with clerical duties, familiarise with the Radiology Imaging System (RIS) for the&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;purpose of patient identification and attendance with appropriate training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4.2 Answer the telephone and deal with enquires as appropriate&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Stock and equipment maintenance.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5.1 Assist with checking and storage of supplies required within the department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5.2 To report equipment faults in an accurate and timely manner to the Modality Lead Radiographer or her Deputy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Personal development. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6.1 &lt;/strong&gt;To participate in the Trust Individual Performance and Development Review&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Scope and Purpose of Job Description&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A job description does not constitute a ‘term and condition of employment’. It is provided only as a guide to assist the employee in the performance of their job. The Trust is a fast moving organisation and therefore changes in employees’ duties may be necessary from time to time. The job description is not intended to be an inflexible or finite list of tasks and may be varied from time to time after consultation/discussion with the post holder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
